            <div type="poem">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1827-28" script="print" medium="ink"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/><hi rend="caps">THE CONSTELLATIONS<lb/><space quantity="4" unit="chars"/>NORTHERN, SOME OF THE ZODIAC AND<lb/><space quantity="4" unit="chars"/>SOME OF THE SOUTHERN</hi></head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l><hi rend="caps">DOST</hi> thou see proud <name type="astronomical" corresp="#VENUSPLANET">venus</name> there</l>
                    <l>Glittering in the evening air<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#VENUSGLOSS"/></l>
                    <pb facs="1229164"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top">22</fw>
                    <l>The belt of <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ORION">orion</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ORIONGLOSS"/> beside it is seen</l>
                    <l>A glorious sight for all sky loving men</l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">5</add>And then red <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MARS">mars</name> appeareth high</l>
                    <l>On his throne upon the sky<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MARSGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Then the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#URSAMAJOR">greater bear</name> is seen</l>
                    <l>Then <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CHARLESSWAIN">charles&#x02BC;s wain</name> with his bright team<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CHARLESSWAINGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Next the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#DRACO">dragon</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#DRACOGLOSS"/> doth appear</l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">10</add>Next <name type="astronomical" corresp="#COMABERENICES">berenices golden hair</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#BERENICESHAIRGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#BERENICESHAIRTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>After that the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CORONABOREALIS">northern crown</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CORONABOREALISGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Then the very fiery <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CYGNUS">swan</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CYGNUSGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#CYGNUSTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Next comes starry <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CHARLESSHEART">charles</name>&#x02BC;s heart<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CHARLESSHEARTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>After that the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TELESCOPIUM">telescope</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TELESCOPIUMTEXTGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#TELESCOPIUMTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">15</add>Next doth come the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#EQUULEUS">little horse</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#EQUULEUSGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>After that the stupid <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ANSER">goose</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ANSERGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Then the very timid <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LEPUS">hare</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LEPUSGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>After that the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#URSAMINOR">lesser bear</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#URSAMINORGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Then doth come the cunning <name type="astronomical" corresp="#VULPECULA">fox</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#VULPECULAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">20</add>Then appears the blessed <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CRUX">cross</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CRUXGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Then we see great <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CHARLESSOAK">charles&#x02BC;s oak</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CHARLESSOAK"/></l>
                    <l>Next I&#x02BC;ll call it <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CRATER">juno&#x02BC;s cup</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CRATERGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#HERCULESCONSTELLATION">Hercules</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#HERCULESGLOSS"/> appeareth high</l>
                    <l>Next <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CERBERUSCONSTELLATION">cerberus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CERBERUSGLOSS"/> in the sky</l>
                    <pb facs="1229165"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top">23</fw>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">25</add>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LACERTA">lizard</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LACERTAGLOSS"/> next to them appears</l>
                    <l>High the pouncing <name type="astronomical" corresp="#AQUILACONSTELLATION">eagle</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#AQUILAGLOSS"/> soars</l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#CEPHEUSCONSTELLATION"><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">C</hi></hi>epheus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CEPHEUSGLOSS"/> and <name type="astronomical" corresp="#BOOTES">bootes</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#BOOTESGLOSS"/> now</l>
                    <l>After that sweet <name type="astronomical" corresp="#APUS">hirundo</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#APUSGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#SWALLOWTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#MONSMAENALUS">Maenalus mountain</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MONSMAENALUSGLOSS"/> next</l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">30</add>Then the furious keen&#x2010;eyed <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LYNX">lynx</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LYNXGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#LYNXTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>High up there is <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SCORPIO">scorpio</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SCORPIOGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>After that the gener<!--overwriting?-->ous <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LEO">leo</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LEOGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CAMELOPARDALIS">cameleopard</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CAMELOPARDALISGLOSS"/> appeareth high</l>
                    <l>Next to it the little <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MUSCA">fly</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MUSCAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">35</add>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SERPENS">serpent</name> <name type="astronomical" corresp="#OPHUCHUS">serpent bearer<!--second e in bearer might be overwriting?--></name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SERPENSGLOSS"/> then<metamark>&#x002A;</metamark><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#SERPENSTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Next to it the butting <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ARIES">ram</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ARIESGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#SCUTUM">Sobieski&#x02BC;s shield</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SCUTUMGLOSS"/> up there</l>
                    <l>After it the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#AURIGA">charioteer</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#AURIGAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TAURUSPONIATOWSKI">bull of poniatowski</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TAURUSPONIATOWSKIGLOSS"/> then</l>
                    x    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">40</add>Next the very longbilled <name type="astronomical" corresp="#GRUS">crane</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#GRUSGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_textual" target="constellations_glosses_textual.php#GRUSTEXTGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#ANTINOUSCONSTELLATION">Antinous</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ANTINOUSGLOSS"/> and <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SAGITTA">arrow</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SAGITTAGLOSS"/> down</l>
                    <l>far below the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CORONAAUSTRALIS">southern crown</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CORONAAUSTRALIS"/></l>
                    <l>THe <name type="astronomical" corresp="#DELPHINUS">dolphin</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#DELPHINUSGLOSS"/> swimming through the air</l>
                    <pb facs="1229165"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top">24</fw>
                    <l>Next to it the gods fire <name type="astronomical" corresp="#ARA">altar</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ARAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">45</add>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CANESVENATICI">hounds</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CANESVENATICIGLOSS"/> <subst><del>s</del><add rend="overwriting">t</add></subst>he bull<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TAURUSGLOSS"/> are seen up there</l>
                    <l>Then doth come great <name type="astronomical" corresp="#NORMA">euclids square</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#NORMAGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LEOMINOR">lesser lion</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LEOMINORGLOSS"/> next we see</l>
                    <l>Next to it the armed <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MUSCABOREALIS">bee</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MUSCABOREALISGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#PERSEUSCONSTELLATION">Perseus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#PERSEUSGLOSS"/> <name type="astronomical" corresp="#PEGASUSCONSTELLATION">pegasus</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#PEGASUSGLOSS"/> then</l> <!--There is a mark after "then" that looks like it may be the start of another letter-->
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">50</add>After it the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CHAMAELEON">chamelion</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CHAMAELEONGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><name type="astronomical" corresp="#ANDROMEDACONSTELLATION">Andromeda</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#ANDROMEDAGLOSS"/> is seen on high</l>
                    <l>Then the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#VIRGO">virgin</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#VIRGOGLOSS"/> in the sky</l>
                    <l>Ten starred <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TRIANGULA">triangle</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TRIANGULAGLOSS"/> doth appear</l>
                    <l>The horn the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MONOCEROS">unicorn</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MONOCEROSGLOSS"/> doth bear</l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">55</add>Shining in golden light he&#x02BC;s drest</l>
                    <l>With a horn instead of a towering crest</l>
                    <l>The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LIBRA">scales</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LIBRAGLOSS"/> in which twas vainly said</l>
                    <l>The crimes and virtues of men <lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>were weighed</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">T</hi></hi>he <name type="astronomical" corresp="#SAGITTARIUS">archer</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#SAGITTARIUSGLOSS"/> with his flying dart</l>
                    <l><add rend="linenumber-left-JR">60</add>I should not think it would pierce the heart</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">T</hi></hi>he <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CANCER">crab</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CANCERGLOSS"/> and the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#GEMINI">twins</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#GEMINIGLOSS"/> with their clothes<lb type="runover" rend="below"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>of fire</l>
                    <l>After them doth come the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#LYRA">lyre3</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#LYRAGLOSS"/><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#RUSKINNOTE2"/><!--page break--></l>
                    <pb facs="1229166"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top">25</fw>
                    <l><!--the page numbers stop on this page-->The <name type="astronomical" corresp="#TRIANGULUMAUSTRALE">little triangle</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#TRIANGULUMAUSTRALEGLOSS"/> appears on high</l>
                    <l><subst><del>a</del><add type="overwriting"><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">A</hi></hi></add></subst>nd the <name type="astronomical" corresp="#CAPRICORN">goat</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#CAPRICORNUSGLOSS"/> that is formed in the arched sky</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">B</hi></hi>ut oh that wonder of them all</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">W</hi></hi>hich <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MILKYWAY">milky way</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MILKYWAYGLOSS"/> europeans call</l>
                    <l>And which the ancients thought the road</l>
                    <l>Which all their best and bravest<!--the r in "bravest" looks more like an n--> trod</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">U</hi></hi>nto great <name type="astronomical" corresp="#JUPITER">Jupiters</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#JUPITERGLOSS"/> blest abode</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">B</hi></hi>right these stars are beauteous gold</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">B</hi></hi>ut let history unfold</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">H</hi></hi>er page of learning let us see</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">W</hi></hi>hether that is not more bright than thee</l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">E</hi></hi>en thou O beauteous <name type="astronomical" corresp="#MERCURY">mercury</name><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="constellations_glosses_contextual.php#MERCURYGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><hi rend="doubleletter-fill"><hi rend="caps">M</hi></hi>uch better than the brightest star</l>
                    <l>Virtue I will say you are</l>
                    <l>Better than knowledge yes indeed</l>
                    <l>Virtue you should have the lead
                    </l>
                    
                    
                </lg>
            </div>
            <!--Simple Drama. Delete this <div/> if not used.-->
            <div type="drama">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="pencil"/>Title of Drama</head>
                <div type="act">
                    <head type="act">Act I</head>
                    <sp>
                        <speaker>Antony</speaker>
                            <stage>(pacing anxiously)</stage>
                            <l>I come to bury Caesar, not to praise him.</l>
                    </sp>
